        "content": "<p>I’m curious about whether the theorem ‘for module over PID, flat and torsion-free are the same thing’ is already in mathlib? If so, what’s the proof stratergy? I’m currently taking a course in homological algebra and it’s sounds like a well-known proof is wrong.</p>",
